03/09/2003
VIENNA, Austria -- Bulgaria launches consultations with Austria Wednesday (3 September) on closing the justice and home affairs chapter of EU accession negotiations. 
The talks will be held in Vienna. 
Bulgaria's minister of European affairs and chief negotiator with the EU, Meglena Kouneva, will lead Sofia's delegation.
In other news, the mayors of the Bulgarian city of Blagoevgrad and the Greek city of Thessaloniki signed a protocol Sunday on economic and cultural co-operation. 
The document envisions joint initiatives and projects in trade and economics, tourism, regional government, environmental protection, education, culture and sports. 
(Trud, 24 Chassa - 03/09/03; BTA, BNR, BNT - 02/09/03)
